INSERT [dbo].[WorkItem] ([Id], [WorkItemTypeId], [Title], [AssignedAccount], [StateId], [AreaId], [Description], [StartDate], [EndDate], [PriorityId], [ClassificationId], [DevelopmentId], [ParentId], [Reason], [Iteration], [RepoSteps], [SystemInfo], [ResolvedReason], [itemPriority], [Severity], [Activity], [OriginEstitame], [Remaining], [Compleated], [BranchId], [FoundInBuild], [IntegratedInBuild], [ReasonId], [RelationId], [RiskId], [BusinessValue], [TimeCapacity], [ValueAreaId], [Effort], [StackRank], [DueDate], [StoryPoints], [AcceptanceCriteria], [IsPublic], [SystemDesignInfo], [ClosedDated]) VALUES (8095, 2, N'Changelog Manager', 1, 1, 1, N'<p>The feature would allow system administrators, project managers and investors to generate changelogs either by manually inputing the changelog themself or by selecting a list of compleated work items in odered to geneerate the changelog. After the changelog is generated it should be bound to a list of changelogs in a descending order. </p>', CAST(N'2020-02-29T22:00:00.000' AS DateTime), CAST(N'2020-03-09T22:00:00.000' AS DateTime), 1, NULL, NULL, 8095, 1, 1004, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N'2', N'', 1, N'10', NULL, CAST(N'2020-03-01T07:39:13.153' AS DateTime), NULL, N'<h1>Changelogs should have the given functionalities</h1><p><br></p><ol><li>Dashboard/Generate Changelog  should open up two panels, the first containing a grid of all closed work item with the option to select multiple work items using a checkbox. After the user makes his choice he can press a button beneath the grid in order to generate a changelog from all the selected workitems. Under the panel with the grid there should be another containing a wyswg editor allow the user to manually input the changelog as well as a button to save it.</li><li>Changelog generator, should be able to take the input from both panels and save the changelog in the database, associate it with the current project and mark all work items as associated with the current changelog if the user used the automatic generator. The Automatic generator should take names of the work items and build a changelog in the following order Changelog {Date} Released modules -&gt; All epics , Features -&gt; all features, Improvements -&gt; all closed tasks, Issues -&gt; all issues, Breaking Changes -&gt; all Bugs, Tests -&gt; all Tests. It should return it to the user for preview with three options, cancel to cancel the current changelog, confirm to save changes and edit to make quick edit of the generated changelog.</li><li>Backlog/ View Changelogs- it should be able to load all changelogs associated with the project with the option of editing each editing a selected changelog.</li><li>Administration/ Changelog integrations- this page would load a detailed guide allowing the user to integrate the Changelog generator with his product page, it would consit of a panel showing his api key, as well a three scripts showing the user how to call our api in order to recieave his cangelog data. Examples should be provided in C#, PHP, Node.Js and Python. The examples should be simple ajax calls that will call our API method HOSTEDURL/Changelog/GetActiveChangelogs it would accept a post method with a model of an api key and project id if both match it would return the changelog as JSON.</li></ol>', NULL, NULL, NULL)
